": that allows you to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"unlock a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRecMutex"},{"type":"text","text":" completely returning the depth, (i.e. the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"number of times this mutex was locked). The depth can later be used","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to restore the state of the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRecMutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" by calling"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_rec_mutex_lock_full()"},{"type":"text","text":". In GLib 2.32, "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRecMutex"},{"text":" has","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"been deprecated in favor of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RecMutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"StaticRecMutex","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"StaticRecMutex"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RecMutex":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/recmutex","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The GRecMutex struct is an opaque data structure to represent a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"recursive mutex. It is similar to a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" with the difference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that it is possible to lock a GRecMutex multiple times in the same","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"thread without deadlock. When doing so, care has to be taken to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unlock the recursive mutex as often as it has been locked."}],"title":"RecMutex","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"RecMutex","